<h3><a id="user-content-dont-be-a-jerk" class="anchor" href="#dont-be-a-jerk" aria-hidden="true"><span class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Don’t Be a Jerk</h3>

<p>DOT’s Don’t Be A Jerk bike safety campaign humorously highlights the essential dos and don’ts of safe, responsible biking. According to DOT’s 2010 Sustainable Streets Index, commuter cycling increased 262% in New York City from 2000 to 2010. With more bikes on the road, smart cycling is even more crucial to making New York City’s streets safer for everyone using them.</p>
